    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>A Grave-Singer is the spectral remnant of a Svellheim mourner, twisted by the blight into an undead spirit. It drifts above the barrows, its mournful dirge draining the will of the living and calling the dead back to service. Where a Grave-Singer sings, Barrow-Draugr rise.</p>",
      "director": "<p>The Grave-Singer is a controller — keep it at range and use Dirge to daze PCs. Grave-Song aura slows any living creature that starts near it, making it hard for melee fighters to close. If a Barrow-Draugr is destroyed, use Raise the Fallen (1/encounter) to bring it back with 15 HP. Incorporeal halves non-magical physical damage — fire and force bypass this. Keep it flying above melee reach when possible.</p>",
